[2] UN chief kicks off tour of Ebola-hit West Africa
Date: Fri 19 Dec 2014
Source: Daily Mail, AFP (Agence France-Presse) report [edited]
http://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/afp/article-2880448/UN-chief-kicks-tour-Ebola-hit-west-Africa.html


UN chief Ban Ki-moon arrived Fri [19 Dec 2014] in Liberia on the 1st stop of a visit to Ebola-ravaged West African countries for a 1st-hand assessment of global efforts to fight the epidemic. Ban, who flew in from Ghana, where the UN Ebola mission [UNMEERS] is headquartered, was welcomed on arrival in Monrovia by Liberian Vice President Joseph Boakai with full military honours. Ban will also travel to Guinea, Sierra Leone and Mali, where the UN is leading the response to the health crisis.... -- more

