Israel pledged an additional USD 8.75 million on Wed [17 Dec 2014] to the UN's Ebola Response Multi-Partner Trust Fund (MPTF) towards fighting the deadly disease, the country's Foreign Ministry said in a statement.

Dr. David Nabarro, Special UN Envoy for Ebola said at a signing ceremony for the pledge that "This donation has put Israel as the 6th largest state to contribute to fighting Ebola, and 1st per capita." ... -- more

